An interactive 3-hour module demonstrating reproducibility principles for best research practices.

# This interactive module has two parts:

<div style="margin-top: 10vh;"></div>

### 1. What is Reproducibility? 

- Reproducibility is the first step towards robust research results

- 4 principles for reproducible research: annotate, automate, hoard, share\
  *Bonus!:* some activities to refresh your R coding skills

#### [I want to learn about Reproducibility](reproducibility_half.html)

<div style="margin-top: 10vh;"></div>

### 2. Git(Hub) streamlines reproducible research practices

- Git and GitHub make it easy to backup, collaborate, and share our research!

#### [I want to learn about Git(Hub)](github_half.html)
